<a name="2596"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">CES Mobile Goes Live - December 8</div>
<br />
CES Mobile is a new mobile phone-based tool that allows exhibitors and attendees to search the online exhibitor directory, view exhibitor listings, build a “Mobile Exhibitor Plan,” find sessions, book a taxi or find a local restaurant. If you have a Windows Mobile&reg;, Palm&reg;, Blackberry&reg;, iPhone&reg;, Symbian&reg; or Java/J2ME handheld device, you can access the tool by simply texting* CESMobile to 41411 to download the application. iPhone users can access the application in their browser after texting CESMobile to 41411.<BR><BR>Navigating CES has never been easier!<BR><BR>*Standard text message and data rates apply.<BR>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2561"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Celebrities at the 2009 International CES</div>
<br />
<IMG height=175 hspace=5 src="/print/images/photos/brianwilliams1.jpg" width=200 align=right vspace=5>NBC Universal will again be the Official Broadcast Partner of the International CES, broadcasting live from the show floor. They will be on hand with select NBC Universal broadcast and cable entities such as: The Today Show, the NBC Evening News with Brian Williams, Access Hollywood and financial expert Maria Bartiromo. <BR><BR>Sony Pictures Television (SPT) will also return to the 2009 International CES show floor in full force, showcasing its wide variety of content across all platforms. In celebration of the 25th anniversary of Jeopardy!, SPT will film daily episodes of Celebrity Jeopardy! on a specially built set on the CES show floor. They will record 11 Jeopardy! episodes throughout CES, on a 16,000-square-foot stage that will become the new set for the game show, in front of an audience of 600. Dr. Oz, a frequent medical guest star on The Oprah Winfrey Show, will also appear in the SPT booth, promoting his new syndicated talk show.<BR><BR>Do you have celebrities making appearances at your booth? Are you planning on live musical performances? Let us know ASAP by e-mailing <A href="mailto:acarney@CE.org" target=_blank>acarney@CE.org</A> so we can post your information on CESweb.org, offering you additional company and booth exposure at no additional cost.<BR>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2560"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Go Global</div>
<br />
<IMG height=159 hspace=10 src="/print/images/content/USCS.jpg" width=150 align=right vspace=5>Are you a U.S. based exhibitor interested in exporting?&nbsp; <BR><BR>The U.S. Department of Commerce’s Commercial Service, in cooperation with CEA, is offering meetings between U.S. exhibitors and consumer electronics industry specialists from U.S. embassies around the world who will be attending the 2009 International CES. If you would like help finding trade partners and succeeding in international markets, then sign up for the <A href="/print/docs/GMIP_for_CES_2009_w_Detailed_Information.pdf" target=_blank>U.S. Commercial Service’s Global Market Insight Program.</A> [link to GMIP pdf attached]

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2559"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">World’s Coolest Tradeshow is Working to Be the Greenest</div>
<br />
<IMG height=46 hspace=10 src="/print/images/content/planetmetrics_logo.jpg" width=150 align=right vspace=10>For more than 40 years, CES has been the place to go for cutting-edge consumer technology. It is, after all, the Consumer Electronics Show. But with such increasing importance being placed on the impact technology has on the environment, the E in CES could just as well stand for “eco-friendly.”<BR><BR>With the help of important partners, including GES, Aramark, the Las Vegas Convention Center (LVCC) and the Sands Expo and Convention Center, CES exhibitors now have more opportunities than ever to recycle while conducting a year's worth of business in one prime, environmentally friendly location. CES is also working with Planet Metrics to calculate it's carbon footprint and investigate opportunities for reforestation and other environmental projects in Nevada.<BR><BR>GES offers several eco-friendly booth packages to help make small responsible changes that amount to a big difference. Check out our <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/docs/GES_Sustainable_Exhibit_Solutions_Order_Form.pdf" target=_blank>Sustainable Exhibit Solutions Order Form</A>, including:<BR>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Insert panels which are <A href="http://www.fscus.org/" target=_blank>Forest Stewardship Council (FSC)</A> certified and are formaldehyde-free</LI>
<LI class=text>Shelves and counters made from formaldehyde-free particle board</LI>
<LI class=text>Eco-friendly carpet</LI></LI></UL><A href="/print/cesgreening.asp" target=_blank>See all the efforts to minimize CES' environmental footprint.</A>

